1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,280
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:22,440
How much coffee did you drink?

3
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,880
Don't you know your limit?

4
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:26,080
Just stop being so cute.

5
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:30,800
<i>Don't push yourself so hard.</i>
<i>I'm worried about you.</i>

6
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,760
- Is this your house?
- I brought Duang with me.

7
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,000
Answer me.

8
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,680
Will you be my boyfriend, Duang?

9
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:40,480
Of course.

10
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:44,880
<i>Through every chapter,</i>
<i>it's always gonna be you, Qin.</i>

11
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,960
<i>It's always gonna be you, Duang.</i>

12
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:59,000
I love you.

13
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,760
What are you looking at?

14
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:08,880
I love you too.

15
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:13,880
I love you too.

16
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:17,960
It's a shame

17
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,760
I didn't get to meet you
back in high school.

18
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,560
And what if you had?

19
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,200
I would've hit on you back then.

20
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:31,000
If we had started dating back then,
we might have broken up.

21
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:33,480
Impossible.

22
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,960
I'd never break up with you.

23
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:38,480
And you can't break up with me either.

24
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,400
No, let's not talk about this.

25
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,720
Thank you for choosing me.

26
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:51,600
We choose each other, Duang.

27
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:57,960
From now on,
I'll devote even more of my love to you.

28
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:01,960
Listen.

29
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:05,400
I'll also love you more and more.

30
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,000
I'm starving.

31
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,440
What time is it?

32
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:23,880
It's 2:00 a.m.

33
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:31,600
Making such a cute face…

34
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,960
Do you want garlic shrimp?

35
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,040
You know me too well.

36
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,400
Well…

37
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:41,640
We'll go to the restaurant
when you're free.

38
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:45,320
For now, let's have instant noodles.
I'll make some for you.

39
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,480
You're spoiling me again.

40
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:50,280
I love to spoil you.

41
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,240
Hurry up

42
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,920
so I can take a shower.

43
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:19,959
You can take a shower now. I'm fine.

44
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,600
You are, but I'm not.

45
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,800
Quickly.

46
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,440
Hurry up,

47
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:46,080
then you can shower after.

48
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,880
You can take your time.

49
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,720
You've got no classes today.

50
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:53,400
I do, but I can be late.

51
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,840
It's fine.

52
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:58,600
You can't be late. I'm coming with you.

53
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,480
Huh?

54
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:06,920
Why are you surprised?
I'm just hanging out with my boyfriend.

55
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,520
Do you have to be this excited?

56
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:19,760
You don't get it.
Are you trying to kill me?

57
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,080
Stop saying that.

58
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,880
If you die, I'll get myself a new lover.

59
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:25,960
You can't!

60
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,600
I don't want that to happen.

61
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,640
Get out already. I'm taking a shower.

62
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:39,400
Okay. I'll leave now.
I won't die anytime soon either.

63
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:42,320
You can only have me
as your sweetheart, alright?

64
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:52,440
I know.
You can't be with anyone else either.

65
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,200
Now get out.

66
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,000
Your shirt actually fits.

67
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,120
One sec.

68
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,320
I love this fragrance on you.

69
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,280
Yours is the same.

70
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,080
Let's take a selfie.

71
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:03,720
Why did you want to take a selfie?

72
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,400
Just take a look.

73
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,320
What's the matter, huh?

74
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,720
I'm fine.

75
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,120
What's wrong?

76
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,600
Huh? I can tell something's wrong.
What's wrong?

77
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,720
Don't tease me.

78
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,560
I'm not teasing you.

79
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,840
Why are you turning away from me?

80
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,000
Aww…

81
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:00,560
It's okay. Don't cry.

82
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,160
Let me get ready first, or you'll be late.

83
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:21,240
<i>So he finally made it official</i>
<i>to his close friends group?</i>

84
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,840
<i>Well, it's like the acting prime minister.</i>

85
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:26,600
<i>You may have the position,</i>
<i>but it's still not official.</i>

86
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,200
<i>You guys are so jealous! Assholes!</i>

87
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:35,480
Can we go now?

88
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,360
Alright. Let's go.

89
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,440
- Hey!
- Whoa!

90
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:53,200
What's the tagged selfie
on Instagram all about?

91
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,360
Seriously? Did you steal his phone
and post it?

92
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,480
He didn't. I typed it myself.

93
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:01,400
- Huh?!
- Huh?

94
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,000
Do you want more snacks?

95
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,680
I'll get some before class starts.

96
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,680
Well, shall we head inside?

97
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,040
Can we sit in the back?

98
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,520
Sure thing.

99
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,920
Qin's acting like he's taking our class.

100
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,200
- Yeah.
- Is the professor strict?

101
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,480
- Huh?!
- Huh?

102
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,640
Why the hell are you guys surprised?

103
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,160
Your shirt looks a bit tight, no?

104
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,200
- Switching up your look?
- Yeah.

105
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,720
Well…

106
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,240
I'm wearing his shirt.

107
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,880
What's weird about wearing
my boyfriend's clothes?

108
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,000
- Huh?!
- Huh?

109
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,440
Me and Qin

110
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:49,760
are now boyfriends.

111
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,400
What did you say?

112
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,840
That made me get up from my seat.

113
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:56,080
So? Want me to repeat that?

114
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:59,120
Me and Qin

115
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,600
are boyfriends now.

116
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:04,280
Qin…

117
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:06,320
I'm so sorry.

118
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,560
- What do you mean by that?
- Ow!

119
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:09,840
I was just kidding.

120
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,440
Congratulations.

121
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:14,200
Took you forever.

122
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:16,880
How do single guys sit in class?

123
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:19,480
Because couples
hold on to each other while studying.

124
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,720
Hey! Can you be gentle?

125
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,480
Here. Take a sip. Drink up.

126
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,280
Students,

127
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,040
when drawing a line,

128
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,760
whether it's a curve, a straight line,

129
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,440
or whatever the fuck it is,

130
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:41,080
how many times have I told you
not to draw it by hand?

131
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,880
<i>Do you still want it?</i>

132
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:45,560
- <i>One just arrived today.</i>
- Instead, what do we use to draw it?

133
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,520
Feelings,

134
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,960
emotions,

135
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,840
inspirations,

136
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,760
and life experiences.

137
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:56,240
<i>I do. How much is it?</i>

138
00:10:58,520 --> 00:10:59,760
<i>I'll pay immediately.</i>

139
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,280
<i>It's 55,000 baht.</i>

140
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:10,360
Express it through your lines.

141
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,320
Put your soul into them.

142
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,200
Pour…

143
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,640
Jamie!

144
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,520
Gosh, what is it, Professor?

145
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,040
I was just resting my eyes.

146
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:25,640
How many years
do you think I've been a professor?

147
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:28,240
Do you know how many students
have used that excuse?

148
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:32,040
Professor, have you ever heard this?

149
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:34,680
"I woke up looking too handsome,
so back to sleep I go."

150
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,360
I've never heard that.

151
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,960
Sounds like it came out of your ass.

152
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,560
Right.

153
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:44,960
Who the hell are you?

154
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,560
You don't look familiar.

155
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,800
You said that

156
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:51,360
we have to draw from inspiration.

157
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,560
That's why I brought
my inspiration to class.

158
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,240
- Sheesh!
- Eww.

159
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:59,480
- Yeah.
- Oh, yeah.

160
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,280
Students, this is a great example.

161
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,000
- Your inspiration?
- Yes.

162
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:04,480
I don't mind that.

163
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:06,800
Just make sure
he doesn't disturb the other students.

164
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,400
Students.

165
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:13,760
Lines are very important.

166
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:17,520
Today, we're drawing a still life…

167
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:20,360
turning an inanimate object
into something lively.

168
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,680
I'm freaking tired.

169
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,160
You, seriously…

170
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:53,440
Why did you force Qin
to sit through class with you?

171
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,440
It wasn't that bad for him.

172
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:58,720
I chose to come here
so we could eat garlic shrimp sooner.

173
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,080
That's true.

174
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:03,320
Let's go eat it, shall we?

175
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:09,960
- Sorry.
- Let's go.

176
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,600
He doesn't give a shit about us.

177
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:27,360
I feel like I've supported him
throughout his love journey.

178
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,880
Since day zero,

179
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,560
it's been the two of us.

180
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,600
How about it?

181
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:35,760
Let's go after him.

182
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,960
What's the hurry, buddy?

183
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,960
You're ditching us
now that you've got Qin?

184
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,680
Who are you guys?

185
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,640
I've never met you two.

186
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,720
Fine, Duang. You asked for this.

187
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,120
Move, Qin.

188
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,240
Please move, Qin.

189
00:13:58,680 --> 00:13:59,840
- Let go!
- Pae, ready?

190
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:00,920
Don't!

191
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,280
One…

192
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,320
Two… Three…

193
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,440
I'm taking Qin to get some garlic shrimp!

194
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,600
"Should I peel the shrimp for you, Qin?"

195
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:13,680
So nosy, you guys.

196
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:18,360
Qin, help me…

197
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:21,040
Help me, please.

198
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,280
- Gosh!
- Come on!

199
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,720
- Do it yourself.
- Do it yourself.

200
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:31,480
Hey!

201
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,760
- That's enough.
- You're gonna fly this time.

202
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,320
One…

203
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,760
Two…

204
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,960
And we're off!

205
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,040
Nothing is by chance.

206
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:34,920
Come on!

207
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,400
You're holding his hand
a bit too tight, no?

208
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:39,240
You want to make it clear, don't you?

209
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:41,680
I'm the first puppy to fly on a plane.

210
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:43,520
The world must know this.

211
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,880
- I'm so jealous of him.
- Yeah.

212
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,680
I want to tease him again.

213
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,280
Okay.

214
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,640
Here you go.

215
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:01,960
We can always order more.

216
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:06,400
It's a weekday,
so why are there so many people?

217
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,160
Excuse me, plates for four people, please!

218
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,400
Right! Coming right up.

219
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,720
How did you get here?

220
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,360
Here are your plates.

221
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,920
- Thanks.
- Want anything else?

222
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,600
What the hell? Go and sit somewhere else!

223
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,000
Shoo! Shoo!

224
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,160
Do you mind if we sit here, Qin?

225
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:38,800
Go ahead.

226
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:40,480
You guys always ruin my moments.

227
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,520
- This is my cue, alright?
- Gosh.

228
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,880
We don't have many moments.
You're going to hog it all?

229
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,080
Yeah.

230
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:48,080
You're the biggest whiner
and crybaby here,

231
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,200
lover boy of Nakhon Pathom.

232
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:52,640
You approached Qin through me,

233
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,520
but now that you're dating,
you chose to keep me in the dark.

234
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:58,240
I was about to tell you,
but I didn't have class today.

235
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:02,440
Duang, you're so lucky
to have Qin as your sweetheart.

236
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:04,599
Yeah, look at him.

237
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:07,000
It's almost impossible to win his heart.

238
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:10,240
You're so lucky that he said yes.

239
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:17,119
Allow me to speak
as lover boy's best friend.

240
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:18,760
Duang is a great guy.

241
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:22,920
Saying no to him is a big mistake.

242
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:27,760
Qin, you pulled a secret rare.
Do you know why?

243
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:30,080
He does everything for you,

244
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,080
treating you like a princess.

245
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,400
You're really lucky, Qin.

246
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:35,000
Duang is the best there is.

247
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:36,720
I'd like to object.

248
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:39,360
My friend Qin is the best.

249
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,320
He doesn't even care about
that Faculty King.

250
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,720
Duang simply lucked out.

251
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,720
Yeah, and soon enough,
Qin will become famous.

252
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:48,320
He'll go nationwide and then go global.

253
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:56,040
Luckier than hitting the jackpot.

254
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,080
- True!
- Right?

255
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,440
- Am I right?
- I agree.

256
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:00,600
Qin is the best.

257
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:03,280
- Idiot!
- Idiot!

258
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:06,360
I'm not going to call you
"unique" anymore!

259
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:08,360
I'm going to call you "idiot"!

260
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,640
Yeah. Idiot.

261
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:14,040
What the heck?

262
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:17,600
- Alright. Dig in.
- Let's it.

263
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:28,200
For what?

264
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:32,440
You're not excited? Look what's inside.

265
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,240
Why'd you get me this?

266
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:07,520
It's expensive.

267
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:11,920
Come on.

268
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,200
Aren't you happy?

269
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:18,800
How much was it?

270
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,960
- It was 50,000 baht?
- Plus 5,000.

271
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:26,200
- Sell it.
- What?

272
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:27,760
You want it, don't you?

273
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:31,920
Do you have any money left?

274
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,480
- A decent amount.
- How much?

275
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,680
Sell it, or else I'll be angry.

276
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,440
No! Listen to me first.

277
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:52,040
It's true that it was expensive,
but I really wanted to give it to you.

278
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:55,200
It's not that I got it for you simply
because you wanted it either.

279
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:58,480
This film camera represents me.

280
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:03,400
When you go out to take photos,
if I can't be there with you,

281
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:07,120
it'll feel like I am.

282
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:14,400
I appreciate that you care,

283
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:17,240
but it's too expensive.

284
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,400
It's not.

285
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:25,600
It's the first gift of our relationship.
On top of that,

286
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:28,040
I'm going to get you a monthiversary gift

287
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:30,880
on the 16th of every month
to celebrate the day we started dating.

288
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:32,120
Don't.

289
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:34,200
Why buy me gifts every month?

290
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:38,800
It's just, 55,000 is too expensive.

291
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:43,400
It's not. Your shoes cost even more.

292
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:45,280
- This is nothing.
- Duang.

293
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,760
Yes?

294
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,360
I know.

295
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:04,800
Return it.

296
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:09,360
It's the first gift
for our relationship, though.

297
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,520
I do want a gift from you,

298
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:14,160
but not if it costs this much.

299
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:17,600
I'm your boyfriend,
and I want to be a good partner to you.

300
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:22,680
You want me to accept
a gift that costs so much?

301
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:23,760
I just can't.

302
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:33,960
Contact the camera store and get a refund.

303
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:38,880
Or sell it around Siam.
Someone might buy it from you.

304
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:42,600
Understand?

305
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,600
I understand.

306
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,680
Does giving him flowers
at the jazz showcase

307
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,840
- feel too simple?
- What will you give him then?

308
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:18,880
A gift basket?

309
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:20,280
How about balloons?

310
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:22,520
How about dressing up as a mascot?

311
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,760
That'd be lovely.

312
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:28,360
If you want to go overboard,
hire a sound truck for the showcase.

313
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:29,680
A sound truck, my ass!

314
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:30,800
No need to be sarcastic.

315
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,320
Glad you caught the sarcasm.

316
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:35,560
What about the 55,000 baht film camera?
Didn't you give it to him?

317
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:37,680
Huh?

318
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:40,040
What kind of camera costs that much?

319
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:41,760
It's a rare model, you know?

320
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:45,040
That's nice
you can afford something like that.

321
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:46,280
You're so rich.

322
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:49,320
If your brother knew about this,
he'd scold you until your next life.

323
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:52,520
I'm not rich.
I was broke after buying the camera.

324
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:56,560
He refused to accept it and told me
to sell it. That's why I have it with me.

325
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,760
Damn, he's ruthless.

326
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:01,600
He did the right thing.

327
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,440
You agree with him?

328
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,960
Why am I in the wrong for doing so much?

329
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:11,360
You knew that it was too much.

330
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:13,760
It's fine if you can afford it.

331
00:23:13,840 --> 00:23:16,800
But if you can't take care of
yourself after buying it,

332
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:18,320
what good does that do?

333
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,480
I want to give it to him.

334
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:23,240
I'm not blaming you
for giving him the gift,

335
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:25,080
but it's the fucking price.

336
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,880
His mom told me to take care of him.

337
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:30,920
You're talking nonsense now.
You call this taking care of him?

338
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,320
Why can't I do this?

339
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:33,600
You don't fucking get it.

340
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:35,280
Yeah, I really fucking don't.

341
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:37,760
Damn it, why are you guys fighting?

342
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:39,960
I'm not fighting.

343
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:43,400
Ask yourself what you've done, Duang.

344
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,880
What kind of fucking camera
costs 55,000 baht?

345
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:47,560
This is more than you can handle.

346
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:49,800
No, why are you mad at him?

347
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,760
I'm not. I'm just warning him.

348
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:53,200
Stop being so stupid.

349
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:02,080
You've never been in a relationship.
You don't get it, Jamie!

350
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:06,320
Duang!

351
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:19,160
Jamie, wait!

352
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:21,880
Damn it.

353
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,680
Duang!

354
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:25,480
Why the hell did you take it out on him?

355
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:27,640
Don't take out
your frustration on your friend.

356
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:30,880
Jamie meant well.

357
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:34,720
Whenever you want something,
he always makes it happen.

358
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:38,280
But when he warns you out of goodwill,
this is how you treat him?

359
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:41,680
Fuck. Let me go check on him first.

360
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:58,480
<i>In your dreams</i>

361
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,800
<i>You're not my</i>

362
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:04,040
<i>Cup of tea</i>

363
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:08,080
<i>Anything we agree</i>

364
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,520
<i>You're not my</i>

365
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:15,840
<i>Cup of tea</i>

366
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:25,960
Qin, can we try again?
You made a little a mistake.

367
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:28,040
You seem distracted.

368
00:25:28,120 --> 00:25:29,400
Right.

369
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,720
One more go, okay?

370
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,040
What is it, Jamie?

371
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:52,200
<i>Qin, I'd like to talk about Duang.</i>

372
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:58,920
Thank you for not accepting
Duang's expensive gift.

373
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,120
Duang's stupid.

374
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,640
<i>He doesn't listen either.</i>

375
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:03,040
You had a fight with him?

376
00:26:03,120 --> 00:26:04,520
<i>Not exactly.</i>

377
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:06,160
The more we talked, the madder I got.

378
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:07,960
So I decided to call you instead.

379
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:15,040
If you're choosing to be with Cheewin,
then go ahead.

380
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:18,280
I'd rather stay away from you

381
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:19,680
and him.

382
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:20,720
Get out.

383
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,760
What's the deal? We're all friends here.

384
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:24,880
Are you nuts?

385
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,400
<i>Don't be mad at him.</i>

386
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:29,720
I'm not exactly mad at him, Qin.

387
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:33,600
But he sees treating someone
to expensive stuff as caring.

388
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,320
We've gotta tell him.

389
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:37,480
<i>He still hasn't sold the camera.</i>

390
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:39,560
<i>He's probably on his way to see you.</i>

391
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:42,480
I'll talk to him.

392
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:43,960
Right, Qin.

393
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:48,920
Come on!

394
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,640
You're acting like a child.

395
00:27:01,840 --> 00:27:04,080
Well, then… Let's take a break for now.

396
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:06,560
Gosh…

397
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,600
Finally.

398
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:08,960
I'm starving.

399
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:11,600
Go eat something then, my friend.

400
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:15,000
We can't go anywhere
until practice is over.

401
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:35,600
Are you tired?

402
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:38,400
No. Let's go sell the camera.

403
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:43,200
We can go now.

404
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:54,440
Can you not make that face?
It's like I've done something wrong.

405
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:58,680
No.

406
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:01,200
What face am I making?

407
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:06,680
Can't bring yourself to sell it?

408
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,800
Aren't you going to tell me how you feel?

409
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:18,600
Well, yes.

410
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:23,240
I really don't want
to sell your first gift.

411
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:27,520
Let it all out.

412
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:30,360
Everything I did for you…

413
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:33,960
I want you to know that I love you.

414
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:37,960
I want to give you
as much of my love as I can.

415
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:40,840
I want you to be happy.

416
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:44,720
Because you feel sorry for me?

417
00:28:49,760 --> 00:28:51,200
I heard you talking to my mother.

418
00:28:57,080 --> 00:28:58,640
It's true that I feel sorry for you.

419
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:02,920
But it's because I love you.

420
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,040
I don't want you to feel sorry for me.

421
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:20,880
Duang.

422
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,760
Can I ask you something?

423
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:24,360
What is it, Kim?

424
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:28,840
Can you stay away from Qin for now?

425
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,680
He can't focus during practice.

426
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:32,800
What do you mean?

427
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:33,960
I'm doing fine.

428
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:37,240
You don't realize you can't focus, do you?

429
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:47,720
It's fine. I'll be waiting patiently.

430
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:56,440
I won't disturb you guys anymore.

431
00:29:58,760 --> 00:30:00,480
This showcase is a serious one.

432
00:30:01,080 --> 00:30:02,760
It affects our grades too.

433
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:05,840
I understand.

434
00:30:11,120 --> 00:30:12,240
That said…

435
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:14,800
I'll head out. Good luck.

436
00:30:26,520 --> 00:30:27,400
Kim.

437
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,640
Why the hell did you say that to Duang?

438
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:32,000
Whatever it is, just tell me.

439
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:36,120
I know you love each other,
but you have to focus on your part.

440
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,560
I know what I'm doing.

441
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:40,160
As for the showcase,
you need to talk to me,

442
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,640
not Duang.

443
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:44,440
He distracts you.
So we have to tell him too.

444
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:49,440
But it's me who has to take
responsibility, not him.

445
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:51,120
I didn't blame him, did I?

446
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:56,640
I'm not someone
who doesn't take responsibility.

447
00:30:58,440 --> 00:30:59,360
On top of that,

448
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:01,320
I'm one of you guys.

449
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:06,880
Right, right.

450
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:08,720
I'm sorry.

451
00:31:11,360 --> 00:31:12,360
I'm sorry too.

452
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:18,520
Duang and I have some issues.

453
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:20,760
We'll sort it out soon.

454
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:25,440
As for the lack of focus,

455
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:27,520
that's on me.

456
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:29,920
Again, I'm sorry.

457
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,880
Let's practice one last time.

458
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,560
Focus this time, okay?

459
00:31:33,640 --> 00:31:36,080
Then, get everything sorted out later.

460
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:40,200
What do you think
after hearing all of that?

461
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:42,320
Was I being too harsh on my friend?

462
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:46,240
You really care
about your friend, don't you?

463
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:48,040
I never knew you had this side.

464
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,400
He's like a brother to me.

465
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,120
It's fun being with him.

466
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:55,800
Also, I'm comfortable around him.

467
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:59,680
If you care about him,
go talk to him nicely.

468
00:31:59,760 --> 00:32:01,840
If you want to say sorry, then go ahead.

469
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:23,640
You suddenly went quiet.
I thought you were doing something.

470
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:29,200
Can a fashion student like you do this?

471
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,440
Tell me.

472
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:34,520
I didn't enroll in the class
when I had the chance.

473
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,360
It looks complicated.

474
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:38,320
Do you want me to teach you?

475
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,960
I'm a pro at this.

476
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,440
First,

477
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,840
make a slip knot.

478
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:59,240
Don't say that I'm teaching you…

479
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:00,800
Well, I am.

480
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:03,520
Huh?

481
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,720
I'm sorry.

482
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:08,360
I got way too into roleplaying.

483
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:09,760
I'm getting serious now.

484
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:11,000
There.

485
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:16,080
What are you making exactly?

486
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,800
It's a scarf for my mother.

487
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,000
I see.

488
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:23,480
Repeat until you're out of yarn.

489
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:26,240
Push it through, loop it over the front,

490
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:28,680
and pull it back to where it was.
Then pull it out.

491
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,120
Yes?

492
00:35:16,200 --> 00:35:18,440
Gosh, it took you forever.

493
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:21,320
I was cleaning.

494
00:35:22,200 --> 00:35:25,280
I thought you were pretending sleep
so you could ignore my calls.

495
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,440
Me?

496
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:31,080
Get on with it already.

497
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,280
I just want to tell you that…

498
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:42,520
What is it?

499
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:44,440
<i>Say it, Jamie.</i>

500
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:47,960
You're going to apologize?

501
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,280
You know me too well.

502
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:02,560
Well…

503
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,360
I'm too good.

504
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:08,920
Right.

505
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:10,840
I'm sorry.

506
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:14,240
<i>I didn't mean to be harsh.</i>

507
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:17,160
It wasn't my intention.

508
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:19,960
<i>I actually meant well.</i>

509
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:22,680
I'm sorry as well

510
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:25,880
for being mean to you.

511
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:28,720
Then we're square.

512
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:31,120
Anything you'd like to tell me?

513
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:36,440
I get what you and Qin meant
as to why you scolded me.

514
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:41,360
Nice, concise, to the point, and sharp.

515
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:43,880
<i>You impressed me, buddy.</i>

516
00:36:43,960 --> 00:36:46,960
Right. You two have made up, haven't you?

517
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:50,120
Love you, Pae.

518
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:52,280
Gosh. That gave me goosebumps.

519
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,560
I love you too, Warrior.

520
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:01,960
Right. Call me if you need anything.

521
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:11,720
Right.

522
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:14,160
I'll call you if I do.

523
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:15,520
Hey, I'll call you as well.

524
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:18,560
Right.

525
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:54,640
QIN IS CALLING YOU

526
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:22,280
Why do you love wearing shorts?

527
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:23,680
It makes me feel things.

528
00:38:25,080 --> 00:38:26,560
They're comfortable.

529
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:28,800
Do you like them?

530
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:35,960
My legs, do you like them?

531
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:39,200
Nonsense.

532
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:46,480
You love kissing my legs in bed.

533
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:48,000
Do you like mine, Jamie?

534
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:51,760
Stop it.

535
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:56,160
Teasing you is
a lot more fun than cooking.

536
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,440
Are we going to eat or what?

537
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:01,280
Why do you love tempting me?

538
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:05,680
I'm not tempting you.
You're the one feeling things.

539
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:10,560
I have a weakness for beautiful legs,

540
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:15,280
especially milky-white ones.
They make me lose it.

541
00:39:34,720 --> 00:39:36,280
I guess

542
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:38,680
I'll have you before dinner,

543
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:39,800
Marvis.

544
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:58,600
No.

545
00:39:58,680 --> 00:40:01,520
I'm not gonna call. I need to hang tough.

546
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:03,040
I can do this.

547
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:04,520
I won't call you.

548
00:40:04,600 --> 00:40:06,400
I won't distract you.

549
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:08,400
Don't do it.

550
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:23,440
<i>Hello, where are you?</i>

551
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:27,720
Are you done?
Do you want me to pick you up?

552
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:28,680
<i>No need.</i>

553
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:30,840
<i>I'm outside your place.</i>

554
00:40:30,920 --> 00:40:31,840
Huh?

555
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:33,200
<i>Outside?</i>

556
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:38,080
<i>Go inside without me.</i>

557
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:39,800
<i>I'll send you the code.</i>

558
00:40:59,000 --> 00:40:59,960
That's cute.

559
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,320
This…

560
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:38,600
You bought it for 55,000 baht, right?

561
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:42,960
If you won't sell it,

562
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:46,760
then let it be
the gift we bought together.

563
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:47,960
How about that?

564
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:51,040
Bought together?

565
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:53,680
Let me split the bill.

566
00:41:55,240 --> 00:41:56,200
Hey, but--

567
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:58,880
I'm accepting the gift
you want to give me.

568
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:01,280
I simply want to split the bill.

569
00:42:02,560 --> 00:42:05,160
Consider this our film camera.

570
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:09,400
Can we do that?

571
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:12,600
Sure.

572
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:14,800
Yes, we can.

573
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:17,400
Give me your QR code.

574
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:18,800
I'm paying you.

575
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:26,360
Duang?

576
00:42:39,240 --> 00:42:40,560
A gift…

577
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:43,600
is anything

578
00:42:43,680 --> 00:42:45,680
that you want to give.

579
00:42:47,080 --> 00:42:50,120
It doesn't have to be expensive.

580
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:53,360
You don't need to make up
for my family too.

581
00:42:55,080 --> 00:42:58,160
Remember the first few days
you were trying to win my heart?

582
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:02,960
<i>You made me a box of chocolates.</i>

583
00:43:03,760 --> 00:43:06,680
<i>Do you remember</i>
<i>what kind of emotion was behind that gift?</i>

584
00:43:07,560 --> 00:43:10,520
- I gave it to you because I wanted to.
- And that's enough.

585
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:14,080
It was special because of that.

586
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:16,960
I get it now.

587
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:21,360
I'll capture a whole bunch
of our memories with this film camera!

588
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:26,440
By the way, give me your LINE ID.

589
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:33,120
It'd be weird
not to exchange IDs as a couple, right?

590
00:43:33,720 --> 00:43:35,200
Here's your boyfriend's LINE ID.

591
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:42,480
Added.

592
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:51,200
How did you know I'm staying here?
How did you know where I live?

593
00:43:52,320 --> 00:43:53,520
Well…

594
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:57,160
Hello, Jamie. Are you with Duang?

595
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:59,320
I'm not with him, Qin.

596
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:01,280
<i>How about looking for him at his place?</i>

597
00:44:04,840 --> 00:44:07,440
I'm hungry. I got us chicken and rice.

598
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:10,560
Let me get plates for us.

599
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:15,360
I'm really happy
that you came to my place.

600
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:17,840
My room without you…

601
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:19,200
It just feels weird.

602
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:24,960
Why?

603
00:44:27,040 --> 00:44:28,640
So you're hooked on me now?

604
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:34,280
Qin?!

605
00:44:35,960 --> 00:44:39,000
You didn't answer my calls,
and you didn't call me back.

606
00:44:39,960 --> 00:44:41,760
- You called me?
- Take a look.

607
00:44:43,600 --> 00:44:44,760
What?!

608
00:44:44,840 --> 00:44:46,120
You did call me!

609
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:48,120
You must've called
when I was getting changed.

610
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:51,200
I was going to text you when I got here,

611
00:44:51,280 --> 00:44:53,280
but I worried I would distract you.

612
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:54,760
Kim said…

613
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:57,040
The jazz showcase is

614
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:59,040
very important to you guys.

615
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:04,240
It was my fault for not being able
to concentrate during practice.

616
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:06,800
I was worried about my boyfriend.

617
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:15,160
I didn't think much of it.

618
00:45:16,560 --> 00:45:17,760
Liar.

619
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:21,760
Well, I kind of did.

620
00:45:24,160 --> 00:45:28,160
I really love you.
I don't want to cause you problems.

621
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:34,960
You aren't the only one in love here.
I love you too.

622
00:45:37,920 --> 00:45:39,200
Also…

623
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:41,640
Can you not just disappear like that?
I'm not used to it.

624
00:45:41,720 --> 00:45:43,640
When I check my Instagram

625
00:45:43,720 --> 00:45:45,960
and there isn't a message from you…

626
00:45:49,440 --> 00:45:50,400
Sure thing.

627
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:53,360
I won't disappear anymore.

628
00:45:54,520 --> 00:45:55,720
You now know that

629
00:45:56,600 --> 00:45:58,680
I love only you, right?

630
00:45:58,760 --> 00:46:01,080
I love you very much.

631
00:46:02,200 --> 00:46:03,240
I do.

632
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:04,880
Even your door code…

633
00:46:06,960 --> 00:46:08,840
It's my birthday.

634
00:46:11,760 --> 00:46:14,240
When I found out your birthday,

635
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:16,680
I got excited and set it as my code.

636
00:46:19,320 --> 00:46:20,880
When are you going to eat?

637
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:22,160
I'm hungry now.

638
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:24,000
Let's eat.

639
00:46:27,280 --> 00:46:30,560
You have no clue
how many things about you I've looked up,

640
00:46:30,640 --> 00:46:32,600
like what you like and dislike.

641
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:35,680
Do you think I don't know?

642
00:46:38,160 --> 00:46:40,520
I scolded you for it. Don't you remember?

643
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:47,920
What are you looking at?

644
00:46:48,520 --> 00:46:49,960
Yeah, you're right.

645
00:46:50,880 --> 00:46:52,320
This time you said it out loud.

646
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:53,640
You want more?

647
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:55,840
I can let you scold me all day.

648
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:57,760
What the fuck are you looking at?

649
00:46:58,480 --> 00:46:59,960
Got any snacks in the fridge?

650
00:47:00,040 --> 00:47:02,080
I don't think so, but I'll check.

651
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:03,360
Don't worry, I'll check.

652
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:12,280
There's beer. Want one?

653
00:47:13,160 --> 00:47:14,080
I do.

654
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:20,160
I'm drinking mine outside.

655
00:47:20,240 --> 00:47:21,480
It hits better.

656
00:47:22,240 --> 00:47:23,480
Come out when you're done.

657
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:50,800
Better watch it though.

658
00:47:50,880 --> 00:47:53,480
I'll devour you the minute you get drunk.

659
00:47:58,600 --> 00:48:00,160
You're the one who needs to watch it.

660
00:48:02,640 --> 00:48:03,720
What do you mean?

661
00:48:04,640 --> 00:48:06,080
You're going to devour me?

662
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:08,800
I'll allow it.

663
00:48:11,680 --> 00:48:12,640
Ridiculous.

664
00:48:14,960 --> 00:48:16,200
<i>Duang.</i>

665
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:36,040
It reminds me of you, so I got it for you.

666
00:48:37,480 --> 00:48:38,840
It's so sweet.

667
00:48:38,920 --> 00:48:40,160
Thank you.

668
00:48:40,240 --> 00:48:42,240
My heart's pounding right now.

669
00:48:43,960 --> 00:48:46,360
This already makes me happy.

670
00:48:49,040 --> 00:48:50,360
By the way…

671
00:48:50,440 --> 00:48:52,360
Why does this remind you of me?

672
00:48:53,240 --> 00:48:54,120
Well…

673
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:57,040
You're always my protector.

674
00:48:58,080 --> 00:49:01,800
So I want this little guy
to protect you on my behalf.

675
00:49:05,480 --> 00:49:08,760
I thought you were going to say
I look like a dog.

676
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:17,560
Whose guitar is that?

677
00:49:19,320 --> 00:49:20,720
It's Funan's.

678
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:22,240
I can't play.

679
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:25,120
I can't play any instruments.
But you can, right?

680
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:33,320
You already look so cool like that.

681
00:49:33,960 --> 00:49:36,520
Can I make some noise?

682
00:49:36,600 --> 00:49:37,880
Enough of that.

683
00:49:44,280 --> 00:49:49,000
<i>Someday, I might walk through time</i>

684
00:49:49,080 --> 00:49:54,040
<i>Where our ticking clocks are aligned</i>

685
00:49:54,120 --> 00:49:59,040
<i>And when time brings us together</i>

686
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:03,960
<i>I'll hold you forever</i>

687
00:50:04,680 --> 00:50:07,640
<i>The one I've been waiting for</i>

688
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:15,240
Right.

689
00:50:15,560 --> 00:50:17,680
When I was at your house,

690
00:50:17,760 --> 00:50:19,720
I saw a massive piano.

691
00:50:19,800 --> 00:50:21,400
What else can you play?

692
00:50:22,200 --> 00:50:23,680
Can you play the violin?

693
00:50:23,760 --> 00:50:25,480
Kind of.

694
00:50:26,520 --> 00:50:29,480
When you say "kind of"
it probably means you're a pro.

695
00:50:29,560 --> 00:50:31,840
Even your mom says that you're talented.

696
00:50:32,760 --> 00:50:34,280
That reminds me.

697
00:50:34,360 --> 00:50:36,520
I tried to be as polite as I could,

698
00:50:37,280 --> 00:50:38,960
but I was too chatty, right?

699
00:50:41,280 --> 00:50:44,720
Fortunately,
that's where we became boyfriends.

700
00:50:49,400 --> 00:50:52,200
On top of that,
we also created new memories there.

701
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:06,680
Did I say something wrong?

702
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:40,920
This is my bedroom.

703
00:52:00,120 --> 00:52:01,880
Actually,

704
00:52:03,040 --> 00:52:05,080
I've never told anyone about this.

705
00:52:08,400 --> 00:52:10,440
But I want to tell you now.

706
00:52:18,880 --> 00:52:20,640
I'm always quiet,

707
00:52:22,520 --> 00:52:25,280
and I refuse to talk
to anyone I'm not close to.

708
00:52:29,160 --> 00:52:30,920
There's a reason for it.

709
00:52:31,960 --> 00:52:32,880
I get it.

710
00:52:33,960 --> 00:52:36,440
You're an introvert. I know that.

711
00:52:37,200 --> 00:52:38,960
No need to hide it.

712
00:52:39,960 --> 00:52:41,560
My mother told you, didn't she?

713
00:52:55,000 --> 00:52:57,280
I was just an ordinary child.

714
00:53:00,760 --> 00:53:02,360
I talked like everyone else.

715
00:53:05,480 --> 00:53:06,840
I was just as curious

716
00:53:07,360 --> 00:53:08,720
as other kids.

717
00:53:10,680 --> 00:53:12,400
<i>The only person I could turn to</i>

718
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:14,320
<i>was my babysitter.</i>

719
00:53:15,480 --> 00:53:17,760
<i>My parents weren't there for me.</i>

720
00:53:20,600 --> 00:53:23,080
What is this called?

721
00:53:25,080 --> 00:53:26,120
An elephant.

722
00:53:27,280 --> 00:53:28,280
Don't know what it is?

723
00:53:30,880 --> 00:53:32,480
How do you say this in Thai?

724
00:53:33,560 --> 00:53:34,640
"Ma."

725
00:53:35,960 --> 00:53:38,920
Are you stupid?
You don't know how to say "horse" in Thai?

726
00:53:40,360 --> 00:53:42,920
- Why does it sound like "mama"?
- Gosh!

727
00:53:46,480 --> 00:53:47,960
Can you just shut up?

728
00:53:48,720 --> 00:53:50,480
Stop asking me questions! So annoying!

729
00:53:50,560 --> 00:53:51,920
- But--
- Gosh!

730
00:53:55,520 --> 00:53:56,520
Why are you crying?

731
00:53:57,840 --> 00:53:58,720
Why are you crying?!

732
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:00,080
Why the hell are you crying?!

733
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:02,920
Gosh!

734
00:54:03,000 --> 00:54:04,360
So annoying!

735
00:54:04,920 --> 00:54:06,200
Stop crying already!

736
00:54:07,960 --> 00:54:09,680
I told you to fucking stop crying!

737
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:11,880
You're not going to stop?

738
00:54:11,960 --> 00:54:13,440
If you keep crying,

739
00:54:13,520 --> 00:54:15,680
I will toss you outside
so that you can cry all day.

740
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:17,680
Stop it already!

741
00:54:35,400 --> 00:54:37,960
Is this what you want? Then go ahead!

742
00:54:39,400 --> 00:54:41,600
Cry all you want!

743
00:54:41,680 --> 00:54:43,880
Cry here, outside the house.

744
00:54:43,960 --> 00:54:45,960
Are you going to stop?!

745
00:54:46,840 --> 00:54:48,520
You're not going to stop?

746
00:54:48,600 --> 00:54:49,520
Fine!

747
00:54:54,200 --> 00:54:57,920
Papa, mama…

748
00:55:02,960 --> 00:55:04,520
Are you going to stop?

749
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:05,960
Are you going to shut up?!

750
00:55:06,800 --> 00:55:09,440
If you don't stop,
I'll shove mud in your mouth.

751
00:55:09,520 --> 00:55:10,760
Are you going to stop?!

752
00:55:41,960 --> 00:55:43,240
Qin.

753
00:55:43,320 --> 00:55:46,920
I have to go out for dinner tonight.
Would you like to come with me?

754
00:55:48,240 --> 00:55:51,120
No? You want to stay here
and play all by yourself?

755
00:55:52,840 --> 00:55:54,960
Well then, stay with Sorn, okay?

756
00:55:59,520 --> 00:56:01,320
Please take care of Qin, Sorn.

757
00:56:01,400 --> 00:56:05,440
It's so nice having you here.
I've been feeling a lot more comfortable.

758
00:56:05,520 --> 00:56:07,400
Stay with us for years to come, okay?

759
00:56:07,480 --> 00:56:09,720
Of course. Don't worry.

760
00:56:09,800 --> 00:56:11,920
I'll take good care of Qin.

761
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:14,200
- I'll leave him to you.
- Understood.

762
00:56:14,280 --> 00:56:15,240
I'll be going now.

763
00:56:27,280 --> 00:56:28,400
If you say anything,

764
00:56:30,160 --> 00:56:31,640
I'll make you eat mud.

765
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:34,960
<i>I couldn't do anything.</i>

766
00:56:35,720 --> 00:56:36,920
<i>I wanted to ask for help,</i>

767
00:56:38,440 --> 00:56:40,720
<i>and every time I called for my parents,</i>

768
00:56:41,720 --> 00:56:42,960
<i>they were never there.</i>

769
00:56:43,680 --> 00:56:46,960
<i>They had no idea who I really was</i>
<i>or what I'd been through.</i>

770
00:56:48,280 --> 00:56:50,800
<i>They knew I wasn't normal,</i>

771
00:56:52,840 --> 00:56:54,840
<i>so they took me to a psychiatrist.</i>

772
00:56:55,560 --> 00:56:57,960
Qin, can you say hello to him?

773
00:57:01,160 --> 00:57:02,200
Hello.

774
00:57:02,760 --> 00:57:04,120
My name is Kao.

775
00:57:04,200 --> 00:57:05,640
What's your name?

776
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:10,600
So…

777
00:57:10,680 --> 00:57:13,880
He rarely talks to anyone but us.

778
00:57:13,960 --> 00:57:16,720
He's a quiet boy. He's not social.

779
00:57:18,760 --> 00:57:21,920
If that's the case,
can I ask you a question?

780
00:57:25,320 --> 00:57:27,200
Is there anything you'd like to tell me?

781
00:57:35,760 --> 00:57:36,960
If that's the case…

782
00:57:37,960 --> 00:57:40,600
May I examine the areas
covered by your clothing?

783
00:57:43,360 --> 00:57:44,280
Under his clothes?

784
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:45,760
Yes.

785
00:57:49,280 --> 00:57:50,560
Qin…

786
00:57:50,640 --> 00:57:51,960
May I take a look, Son?

787
00:57:58,640 --> 00:57:59,520
Honey…

788
00:57:59,600 --> 00:58:01,120
What's this?

789
00:58:02,160 --> 00:58:03,120
Qin?

790
00:58:04,040 --> 00:58:05,640
What happened to you?

791
00:58:07,320 --> 00:58:09,200
Honey, check the security cameras.

792
00:58:27,080 --> 00:58:28,640
Oh, dear!

793
00:58:28,720 --> 00:58:29,960
Look at this…

794
00:58:33,320 --> 00:58:34,720
You want to cry, right?!

795
00:58:35,360 --> 00:58:36,840
Cry all you want!

796
00:58:37,680 --> 00:58:40,000
Go ahead! Cry here…

797
00:58:43,160 --> 00:58:45,000
You're home early.

798
00:58:45,080 --> 00:58:46,280
Qin.

799
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:48,440
Wait for me upstairs, okay?

800
00:59:05,320 --> 00:59:06,920
What exactly is this?

801
00:59:07,000 --> 00:59:09,040
But there shouldn't be any cameras here…

802
00:59:09,120 --> 00:59:10,800
Why did you do that?!

803
00:59:11,320 --> 00:59:12,720
I… I didn't mean to.

804
00:59:13,480 --> 00:59:14,720
Pack up your things

805
00:59:15,320 --> 00:59:16,680
and get out of my house!

806
00:59:16,760 --> 00:59:19,360
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

807
00:59:19,960 --> 00:59:21,440
I'm so sorry.

808
00:59:21,520 --> 00:59:22,800
I didn't mean to do it.

809
00:59:22,880 --> 00:59:23,960
Go and get your stuff

810
00:59:25,040 --> 00:59:27,000
before I call the police.

811
00:59:29,080 --> 00:59:30,800
He's an insufferable brat!

812
00:59:30,880 --> 00:59:33,800
He never listens.
What the hell was I supposed to do?

813
00:59:33,880 --> 00:59:37,440
If you care about him that much,
then take care of him yourselves!

814
00:59:38,960 --> 00:59:40,120
You want to know something?

815
00:59:41,080 --> 00:59:43,680
Even a dog knows
how to be grateful when you feed it,

816
00:59:43,760 --> 00:59:44,760
unlike you.

817
00:59:44,840 --> 00:59:45,960
Want to know something?

818
00:59:47,040 --> 00:59:49,160
Even a dog loves its puppies,

819
00:59:49,240 --> 00:59:51,120
unlike you two.

820
00:59:52,640 --> 00:59:56,120
Hiring you to take care of our son
doesn't mean that we don't love him.

821
00:59:56,200 --> 00:59:58,720
We both work extremely hard

822
00:59:58,800 --> 01:00:00,360
to pay for his tuition.

823
01:00:00,440 --> 01:00:03,080
When he grows up, I'm going to teach him

824
01:00:03,160 --> 01:00:05,240
how to be grateful to others.

825
01:00:05,320 --> 01:00:06,240
A quality you lack.

826
01:00:06,320 --> 01:00:08,120
Your parents must've never taught you.

827
01:00:08,200 --> 01:00:09,520
Don't fucking preach to me!

828
01:00:10,440 --> 01:00:12,760
I hope you have time to fucking teach him.

829
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:15,680
You've got it all,
money, status, everything.

830
01:00:16,160 --> 01:00:17,600
But you can't even raise your son!

831
01:00:17,680 --> 01:00:19,720
He must really love you guys!

832
01:00:20,280 --> 01:00:21,600
Keep treating him like this,

833
01:00:21,680 --> 01:00:24,040
and your son
will end up a problematic child.

834
01:00:24,120 --> 01:00:26,240
Education is important.

835
01:00:26,320 --> 01:00:27,560
Good!

836
01:00:27,640 --> 01:00:32,400
Good. Have him study hard
so that he'll get to meet other people.

837
01:00:32,960 --> 01:00:34,800
After classes,

838
01:00:34,880 --> 01:00:37,240
he'll get to meet friends
who have good parents.

839
01:00:37,320 --> 01:00:39,640
Parents who wait
at school to take them home.

840
01:00:39,720 --> 01:00:42,160
He'll be the only one

841
01:00:42,240 --> 01:00:44,640
who has a babysitter and driver.

842
01:00:46,560 --> 01:00:47,480
Here's the kicker.

843
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:49,360
He won't see his parents
when he gets home!

844
01:00:49,440 --> 01:00:51,600
Gosh, what a happy family!

845
01:00:51,680 --> 01:00:52,960
It's as if he were an orphan!

846
01:00:53,520 --> 01:00:54,920
I'm curious.

847
01:00:55,440 --> 01:00:56,600
How will he turn out--

848
01:00:56,680 --> 01:00:57,640
Are you done talking?

849
01:00:59,160 --> 01:01:00,280
If you are, then get out.

850
01:01:00,360 --> 01:01:02,320
No need to tell me!

851
01:01:02,400 --> 01:01:04,760
I'm leaving for sure!

852
01:01:04,840 --> 01:01:07,560
I'm saying this
because I want your son to hear it too!

853
01:01:07,640 --> 01:01:09,800
Even when I'm gone,

854
01:01:09,880 --> 01:01:12,000
you still won't get to be
with your damn parents!

855
01:01:12,080 --> 01:01:13,880
That's enough. Let's go.

856
01:01:13,960 --> 01:01:15,280
Where are you going, ma'am?

857
01:01:15,360 --> 01:01:16,640
I'm not done here.

858
01:01:16,720 --> 01:01:18,440
Can't handle the truth?

859
01:01:18,520 --> 01:01:20,600
I told you to get out of my house!

860
01:01:20,680 --> 01:01:22,400
- Get out!
- <i>What I wanted was</i>

861
01:01:22,960 --> 01:01:24,560
<i>a hug from my parents.</i>

862
01:01:26,120 --> 01:01:27,400
<i>I wanted them to be with me,</i>

863
01:01:27,480 --> 01:01:30,640
<i>to give me love,</i>
<i>like a normal family would.</i>

864
01:01:33,320 --> 01:01:34,720
I never got any of that.

865
01:01:37,200 --> 01:01:38,960
They fired the babysitter

866
01:01:40,720 --> 01:01:42,760
and pretended like nothing ever happened.

867
01:01:49,480 --> 01:01:51,160
They never once hugged me.

868
01:02:06,320 --> 01:02:07,640
How about this?

869
01:02:10,960 --> 01:02:13,240
I don't know if it will work for you,

870
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:16,000
but if your past memories

871
01:02:16,640 --> 01:02:17,960
hurt you…

872
01:02:23,440 --> 01:02:25,640
It's time to stop holding
your younger self's hand…

873
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:37,480
and hold mine.

874
01:02:39,560 --> 01:02:41,000
I'll take it from here.

875
01:03:04,760 --> 01:03:07,520
<i>I was just an ordinary child.</i>

876
01:03:08,240 --> 01:03:10,200
<i>I talked like everyone else.</i>

877
01:03:11,080 --> 01:03:13,360
<i>What I wanted was</i>

878
01:03:15,160 --> 01:03:17,360
<i>a hug from my parents.</i>

879
01:03:19,680 --> 01:03:21,280
<i>Why the hell are you crying?!</i>

880
01:03:21,960 --> 01:03:24,200
<i>I only want the best for him.</i>

881
01:03:24,960 --> 01:03:25,960
<i>Stop crying already!</i>

882
01:03:28,080 --> 01:03:29,360
<i>That hurt like hell back then.</i>

883
01:03:29,440 --> 01:03:31,200
<i>You can now explain how you feel?</i>

884
01:03:31,280 --> 01:03:33,520
<i>- I wanted to cry…</i>
<i>- Try crying one more time.</i>

885
01:03:33,600 --> 01:03:36,800
<i>Gosh, what a happy family!</i>
<i>It's as if he were an orphan!</i>

886
01:03:36,880 --> 01:03:38,480
<i>He rarely talks…</i>

887
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:40,360
<i>You said nothing back then.</i>

888
01:03:40,440 --> 01:03:43,680
<i>- Mama, papa…</i>
<i>- I told you to shut up!</i>

889
01:03:43,760 --> 01:03:45,360
<i>I thought…</i>

890
01:03:45,440 --> 01:03:47,880
<i>Qin probably wouldn't</i>
<i>remember those things.</i>

891
01:03:47,960 --> 01:03:50,360
<i>It's time to stop holding</i>
<i>your younger self's hand.</i>

892
01:04:08,720 --> 01:04:10,200
I promise you…

893
01:04:13,000 --> 01:04:14,960
I'll always be right by your side.

894
01:04:20,400 --> 01:04:22,600
I'll be everything for you.

895
01:04:28,440 --> 01:04:30,160
Walk with me, Qin.

896
01:05:04,640 --> 01:05:06,280
Don't cry, okay?

897
01:06:05,560 --> 01:06:07,000
Your parents love you.

898
01:06:07,760 --> 01:06:09,240
They came back so quickly.

899
01:06:09,320 --> 01:06:13,080
You said you wanted us to be with you.

900
01:06:13,160 --> 01:06:14,600
Is everything okay?

901
01:06:14,680 --> 01:06:16,040
<i>Thank you, Duang,</i>

902
01:06:16,120 --> 01:06:18,160
<i>for always sticking by my side.</i>

903
01:06:18,760 --> 01:06:20,960
<i>Do you think people outside will know</i>

904
01:06:21,040 --> 01:06:23,120
I'm teasing you?

905
01:06:23,200 --> 01:06:25,240
I want to invite you over for a meal.

906
01:06:25,320 --> 01:06:28,640
- I'm back!
- Calm down.

907
01:06:28,720 --> 01:06:29,800
This is my boyfriend.

908
01:06:29,880 --> 01:06:31,200
He is…

909
01:06:32,000 --> 01:06:33,680
Taking a shower together

910
01:06:33,760 --> 01:06:35,480
helps save the environment.
